SIMPLE: respondent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Respondent
<hw>Re*spond"ent</hw> <pr>(-<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>respondens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>respondere</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Disposed or expected to respond; answering; according;
corresponding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wealth <qex>respondent</qex> to payment and contributions.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Respondent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Respondent
<hw>Re*spond"ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pondant</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who responds. It
corresponds in general to <xex>defendant</xex>.</def> Specifically:
<sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who answers in certain suits or
proceedings, generally those which are not according to the course of
the common law, as in equity and admiralty causes, in petitions for
partition, and the like; -- distinquished from
<xex>appellant</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who maintains a thesis
in reply, and whose province it is to refute objections, or overthrow
arguments; -- distinguished from <xex>opponent</xex>.</def> <rj><au>I.
Watts. </au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1228 --></p>

<p><ent>Respondentia</ent>⟦br⟧
